id: pm-dmum
title: "SDK + CLI: render extension/package surfaces to Markdown reference docs (renderExtensionSurfaceMarkdown + describe --markdown)"
description: "Complete the describe verb's missing render leg: the SDK can enumerate WHAT a package contributes (ExtensionActivationSummary via describeExtensionActivation [pm-16ue] / describeExtensionBlueprint [pm-tlpv], surfaced to the CLI by pm extension/package describe [pm-l4c8]) but there is NO way to render that to human-readable Markdown. Package authors today hand-write the README 'Commands & capabilities' reference, which silently drifts from the registered surface.\n\nScope (one PR):\n(1) SDK PRIMITIVE renderExtensionSurfaceMarkdown(summary: ExtensionActivationSummary, options?) -> string, a pure deterministic renderer in core/extensions, re-exported from the SDK barrel. Package authors call it on describeExtensionBlueprint(blueprint) output to generate a drift-free README reference section in their build/test step.\n(2) CLI pm extension describe --markdown / pm package describe --markdown emits a composed Markdown document (per-extension sections + union), following the established pm context/next/guide --format markdown precedent (renderer is a pure function of the structured result; markdown is a CLI presentation format, MCP keeps returning structured data).\n(3) Contracts (EXTENSION_FLAG_CONTRACTS + COMMAND_ARG_CONTRACTS describe/lifecycle, regen full.json), shell completion (bash/zsh/fish), docs (SDK.md + EXTENSIONS.md), and 100% test + docstring coverage.\n\nPhilosophy fit: project management = context management — a package's contributed surface documented automatically from a single source of truth, never drifting. Token-efficient: agents authoring packages emit a README reference without restating the registry."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[8]: agent-ux,"area:cli","area:extensions","area:packages","area:sdk",dx,living-map,pm-cli
