risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Implemented renderExtensionSurfaceMarkdown core primitive + SDK barrel export + CLI describe --markdown (extension & package) + contracts/completion/docs + 100% tests. Markdown is a CLI presentation format (consistent with pm context/next/guide); MCP describe keeps returning structured data which a caller can hand to the SDK primitive.
expected_result: Package authors and agents can generate a drift-free Markdown reference for any blueprint (SDK renderExtensionSurfaceMarkdown on describeExtensionBlueprint output) or installed package (CLI describe --markdown) from the same ExtensionActivationSummary the assert*/run* helpers verify.
actual_result: "Verified in a temp dir: pm package describe <name> --markdown emits the reference doc (loaded/activation-failed/not-loaded status labels correct), the union section spans multiple extensions, --json+--markdown and --markdown on a non-describe action both exit 2 (USAGE), the toon/json paths are unchanged, and renderExtensionSurfaceMarkdown is callable from the built dist SDK barrel. 100% coverage on the new core module, the describe composer, and the register-setup dispatch."
